Nigeria’s Budget for Capital Investments Isn’t Enough, Okonjo-Iweala Says

-- B y   D u l u e   M b a c h u
-- 
2011-07-06T11:47:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-06/nigeria-s-budget-for-capital-investments-isn-t-enough-okonjo-iweala-says.html
Nigeria ’s 2011 spending plans
allocate “almost 74 percent” to recurrent expenditure, leaving
the share for  capital investment  inadequate, Cabinet nominee and
managing director of the  World Bank , Ngozi Okonjo-Iweala, said
at a Senate confirmation hearing today in the capital, Abuja.  “We need to make sure the recurrent doesn’t eat up
everything in the budget,” she said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
